---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Shot from "../components/Shot.astro";
---

<Base
    title="Magritte — Ceci n'est pas Magit."
    description="Magritte is a fast, keyboard-first Git client inspired by Magit: the status-centered workflow as a standalone macOS app, no Emacs required."
    tocDepth={2}
>
    <p class="tagline"><em>Ceci n'est pas Magit.</em></p>

    <p class="lede">
        A fast, keyboard-first git client in the spirit of
        <a href="https://magit.vc/">Magit</a>—no Emacs required.
    </p>

    <p>
        Magritte is written in Rust using <a href="https://gpui.rs/">gpui</a>,
        the framework that powers <a href="https://zed.dev/">Zed</a>. Magritte's
        asynchronous core ensures that it gracefully handles large repos and
        stays responsive even during slow git operations.
    </p>

    <Shot
        name="status"
        width={730}
        height={702}
        alt="Magritte's status view on its own repository: untracked, unstaged, and staged sections, an expanded file diff with a syntax-highlighted hunk, and recent commits"
    />

    <h2>Installation</h2>
    <p>Via homebrew:</p>
    <div class="copyable">
        <pre
            class="shell"><code><span class="prompt">$ </span>brew install lyallcooper/magritte/magritte</code></pre>
        <button class="copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy command">
            <svg
                class="icon-copy"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                aria-hidden="true"
                ><rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"
                ></rect><path
                    d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"
                ></path></svg
            >
            <svg
                class="icon-check"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline
                ></svg
            >
        </button>
    </div>
    <p>
        Or download a binary from <a
            href="https://github.com/lyallcooper/magritte/releases/">GitHub</a
        >.
    </p>

    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>
    <p>After installation, launch Magritte from your terminal:</p>

    <pre
        class="shell"><code><span class="dim"># Open the repo you're in</span>
<span class="prompt">$ </span>magritte

<span class="dim"># Or pass a repo to open</span>
<span class="prompt">$ </span>magritte /dev/my-project</code></pre>
    <p>
        The main screen is the <em>status view</em>. It presents <code>git
        status</code> information, such as untracked, unstaged, and staged
        files. It also shows your stashes, unpushed/unpulled changes, recent
        commits and <a href="/docs/config/#status-sections">more</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
        Use <kbd>j</kbd> / <kbd>k</kbd> to move. Press <kbd>Tab</kbd> on a file name
        in the status view to expand its diff. Stage and unstage changes using <kbd
            >s</kbd
        > and <kbd>u</kbd>. Open the commit menu with <kbd>c</kbd>.
    </p>
    <div class="callout">
        <div class="callout-title">Wondering what's possible?</div>
        Press <kbd>?</kbd> or click the <code>?</code> icon in the bottom right
        to bring up the interactive, context-aware help menu. It shows all the
        actions you can take. It's helpful!
    </div>
    <p>
        Use <kbd>v</kbd> to enter the ever-useful multi-line visual selection mode.
        Use it to act on multiple files at once. You can even use it to surgically
        target specific lines within a diff hunk to act on.
    </p>
    <p>
        The default keymap uses vim-like (emacs-evil) keybindings. If you prefer
        traditional emacs-style, change the Keybindings to "Vanilla" from the
        settings screen (accessible via <kbd>,</kbd>). You can also set the <code
            >keymap_preset</code
        > to <code>"vanilla"</code> in the <a href="/docs/config#key-mappings">config file</a
        >.
    </p>

    <h3>Basic keybindings, vim-style (default)</h3>
    <div class="keys">
        <div>
            <span class="k"><kbd>j</kbd> / <kbd>k</kbd></span> Move down / up
        </div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>c</kbd></span> Commit menu</div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>Tab</kbd></span> Expand / collapse</div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>b</kbd></span> Branch menu</div>
        <div>
            <span class="k"><kbd>s</kbd> / <kbd>u</kbd></span> Stage / unstage
        </div>
        <div>
            <span class="k"><kbd>p</kbd> / <kbd>F</kbd></span> Push / pull menu
        </div>
        <div>
            <span class="k"><kbd>x</kbd></span> Discard (prompts for confirmation)
        </div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>l</kbd></span> Log menu</div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>:</kbd></span> Search all commands</div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>?</kbd></span> Help menu</div>
    </div>

    <h3>Basic keybindings, vanilla emacs-style</h3>
    <div class="keys vanilla">
        <div>
            <span class="k"><kbd>ctrl-n</kbd> / <kbd>ctrl-p</kbd></span> Move down
            / up
        </div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>c</kbd></span> Commit menu</div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>Tab</kbd></span> Expand / collapse</div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>b</kbd></span> Branch menu</div>
        <div>
            <span class="k"><kbd>s</kbd> / <kbd>u</kbd></span> Stage / unstage
        </div>
        <div>
            <span class="k"><kbd>P</kbd> / <kbd>F</kbd></span> Push / pull menu
        </div>
        <div>
            <span class="k"><kbd>k</kbd></span> Discard (prompts for confirmation)
        </div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>l</kbd></span> Log menu</div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>alt-x</kbd></span> Search all commands</div>
        <div><span class="k"><kbd>?</kbd> / <kbd>h</kbd></span> Help menu</div>
    </div>

    <h2>Transient menus</h2>
    <p>
        Magit and Magritte are both built upon keyboard-driven <i
            >transient command menus</i
        >, or transients for short. Transients guide you towards your goal by
        showing you the available options and actions you can take.
    </p>

    <figure class="shot">
        <Shot
            name="tag"
            width={730}
            height={500}
            alt="The tag transient menu open at the bottom of the status view, showing its argument switches (force, annotate) and actions (tag, release, delete) beside their keys"
        />
        <figcaption>
            The tag transient <kbd>t</kbd>
        </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
        Transients are customizable. See the relevant <a
            href="/docs/config/#transients-menu-keys">docs section</a
        >.
    </p>

    <h2>Configuration</h2>
    <p>
        You can configure essentials from the settings screen (accessible via <kbd
            >,</kbd
        >). More advanced settings and custom commands are configurable via the
        <code>config.toml</code> config file. See the <a href="/docs/config/"
            >configuration docs</a
        > for more details.
    </p>

    <h2>Status</h2>
    <p>Magritte is under active development. Current limitations:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            macOS on Apple silicon is the supported release target; Linux x86_64
            builds are best effort.
        </li>
        <li>Release builds are ad hoc signed, not notarized.</li>
        <li>
            Paths that are not valid UTF-8 may display with replacement
            characters.
        </li>
        <li>
            Requires <code>git</code> on your <code>PATH</code>; it refreshes on
            focus and after its own commands rather than watching the
            filesystem.
        </li>
    </ul>
</Base>

<style>
    .tagline {
        margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 1.25em;
    }

    .lede {
        font-size: 1.05em;
        max-width: 40rem;
    }

    /* Key reference: two columns where they fit, one on narrow screens */
    .keys {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(17rem, 1fr));
        column-gap: 3rem;
        max-width: 42rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
        font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .keys > div {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.6rem;
        align-items: baseline;
        padding: 0.35rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .keys .k {
        flex: 0 0 4.5rem;
        white-space: nowrap;
    }

    /* Vanilla's chords (ctrl-n / ctrl-p) need a wider key column. */
    .keys.vanilla .k {
        flex-basis: 8.5rem;
    }

    .shot {
        margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    /* The frame is a component (its styles are scoped there); reach in to
       drop its margin inside a captioned figure. */
    .shot :global(.window) {
        margin: 0;
    }

    .shot figcaption {
        margin-top: 0.6rem;
        text-align: center;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        font-style: italic;

        kbd,
        code {
            font-style: normal;
        }
    }

    /* Hand-written shell blocks: prompts and comments recede, commands read.
       The prompt is unselectable so copied commands don't drag a `$` along. */
    .shell .dim {
        color: var(--muted);
    }

    .shell .prompt {
        color: var(--muted);
        user-select: none;
    }

    .copyable {
        position: relative;
    }

    .copyable .copy {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        transform: translateY(-50%);
        right: 0.75rem;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        color: var(--muted);
        background: var(--bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 4px;
        padding: 0.3rem;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .copyable .copy svg {
        width: 0.9rem;
        height: 0.9rem;
    }

    .copyable .copy:hover {
        color: var(--fg);
        border-color: var(--muted);
    }

    .copyable .copy .icon-check,
    .copyable .copy.copied .icon-copy {
        display: none;
    }

    .copyable .copy.copied .icon-check {
        display: block;
        color: var(--green);
    }

    @media (max-width: 40rem) {
        .copyable .copy {
            display: none;
        }
    }
</style>

<script>
    for (const button of document.querySelectorAll(".copyable .copy")) {
        button.addEventListener("click", async () => {
            const code = button
                .closest(".copyable")
                ?.querySelector("code")
                ?.cloneNode(true) as HTMLElement | undefined;
            if (!code) return;
            code.querySelectorAll(".prompt, .dim").forEach((el) => el.remove());
            await navigator.clipboard.writeText(code.textContent?.trim() ?? "");
            button.classList.add("copied");
            setTimeout(() => button.classList.remove("copied"), 1500);
        });
    }
</script>
